---
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Case study for Chris Tsai's enterprise intranet systems and internal workflow development."
    />
    <title>Enterprise Intranet Case Study | Chris Tsai</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="Chris Tsai home">
        <span>CT</span>
        <strong>Chris Tsai</strong>
      </a>
      <nav aria-label="Primary navigation">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/projects/light-show/">Light Show</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/as006sa" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="case-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Internal Systems Case Study</p>
        <h1>Enterprise intranet systems for workflows, assets, approvals, and operations.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          This case study summarizes private company work at an architecture and workflow level. It avoids internal URLs, data, screenshots, credentials, and confidential process details.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href="/">Back to portfolio</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section detail-grid">
        <aside class="fact-panel">
          <h2>Project Facts</h2>
          <dl>
            <div>
              <dt>Type</dt>
              <dd>Enterprise intranet and workflow modules</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Role</dt>
              <dd>Feature development, optimization, and maintenance</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Stack</dt>
              <dd>Vue 3, Vite, FastAPI, Python, database-backed APIs, Element Plus, PrimeVue</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Scope</dt>
              <dd>Approval flows, forms, permissions, file handling, reporting, and operational data views</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </aside>

        <article class="article-body">
          <h2>Context</h2>
          <p>
            Internal operations often start as spreadsheets, emails, shared folders, and manual follow-ups. The engineering challenge is not only building screens, but encoding business rules into a system that people can trust and maintain.
          </p>

          <h2>Modules Delivered</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>OKR evaluation and workflow redesign.</li>
            <li>ECN engineering change notification process.</li>
            <li>Overtime request and effectiveness tracking.</li>
            <li>Foreign business trip request and reimbursement workflow.</li>
            <li>Project code management and role delegation.</li>
            <li>Asset QR code labels, asset inventory, history tracking, and equipment maintenance.</li>
            <li>BOM version control and operational pricing tools.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Engineering Problems</h2>
          <p>
            These systems required careful treatment of form states, approval stages, user permissions, file attachments, version history, searchable tables, exports, and changes requested by business users after real usage.
          </p>

          <h2>Implementation Focus</h2>
          <p>
            I worked with Vue-based interfaces, reusable business forms, FastAPI endpoints, database-backed data models, and UI libraries suitable for dense internal tools. The goal was clarity, traceability, and fast daily operation rather than decorative UI.
          </p>

          <h2>What This Shows</h2>
          <p>
            This work demonstrates that I can understand messy operational requirements, translate them into system behavior, and keep improving production tools after users begin relying on them.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
